,Recommended,224480,22805907,"Posted: 4 May, 2016",all,Daddy&playgolfwithyourfriends,"Octodad: Dadliest Catch  isn't just another silly casual game with purposely goofy controls and a gimmick that dies out after five minutes.Octodad is more than that. There's a story behind it, and a pretty nice message too.I don't normally write reviews, but I felt like I had to for this game because I feel like I could personally relate to it in my own little way. Although this is purely subjective I believe that behind the story is possibly one of the most powerful messages about love and acceptance.If you want to hear my conclusion of the message behind the story then read the spoilers below.Throughout the entire story Octodad is trying to hide his identity as an Octopus in his attempt to fit in with the humans and keep his happy family together. All through the game he messes up, he's a walking disaster, he can't do anything without destroying half of the things in his path, you can hear people talking about his ""sliminess"" and general negative comments, along with the chef constantly trying to kill him.I think we've all felt like this at times, and maybe even wondered if we're worthy of love if this is all we do and so many people dislike us.  but his family still love him. They still love this ""Slimy"" ""disgusting"" octopus-man even though nobody else, and possibly himself understood why. They saw the good in this kind and caring being that he most likely didn't and loved him despite his octo-flaws. I guess you could say they also gave him a reason to believe in himself, to defy the odds and ultimately reveal his true self to his family, to love himself exactly the way he is and live that happy life we're all searching for. Ultimately I believe that although many negative comments and hurt may be thrown our way by other people, it doesn't make the good we and others see in ourselves any less real.I dedicate this review to my wonderful girlfriend, who saved me like Octodad's family saved Octodad.10/10"
