,Recommended,224480,9002580,"Posted: 6 February, 2014",all,[ Chao ],"Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a game that ended up being quite a bit more then it appeared on the surface. The main lure of this game is its controls, which are both frustrating and hilarious. Many times I would find myself at a difficult point of the game, but still be laughing my♥♥♥♥♥off and cracking jokes as I flailed about helplessly. What surprised me was the quality of the story and writing the game presented, creating a funny yet heartwarming story of a man who loves his family...who just so happens to be an octopus. I espically love when the game gets descriptive of Octodad's 'blurbs' or the often odd banter of background characters. While the game's story is 'short' by how much content it has, the game's difficulty, its replayability with speed runs and collectables, the Co-Op gameplay, and its custom levels with the Steam Workshop make sure that this game can entertain for a long time.Overall, this game is absolutely amazing for a simple indie title. The controls are as fun as they are frustrating, the story is impressive, creating well-written characters and a world that is both mundane and yet slightly off at the same time, and there are a lot of oppertunities for replayability. My only issue is with ONE section of the game which, while it progresses for the story's sake, is a change in the gameplay I wasn't too found of. But it's a minor thing at best and doesn't take anything away from this beautiful expierence in the life of a true family man (and not an octopus). (9/10)I am a human reviewer and totally NOT an octopus."
