76561197993891197,Recommended,224480,9066302,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,CtrlAltDestroy,"(I should note that this was one of the first decent-looking games to hit Steam Greenlight back when it was first new, and I've had my eye on it for about a year and a half. I feel like this game would have had more of an impact if the whole Surgeon Simulator thing hadn't happened by the time it was finally released.)In short: it's a game about an octopus who knocks lots of things over while trying to do mundane things like a normal human would. And somehow it manages to be touching.The base game is only about 3 hours long, but there's so much polish and passion and humor packed into this game that I just can't help but say I enjoyed my time. There are several dozen clever references to other indie games and geek culture, and if that's not your kind of humor, there is also a constant stream of genuinely witty dialogue from the characters.There are some tough parts in later levels, but there is always a way to cheese past them easily if you're observant. And there are lots of extras to find that will easily boost the playtime to 10 hours and beyond.In all, an excellent entry into the ""Slapstick Physics"" genre, and I recommend it to anyone who hasn't given this genre a try yet. Though I probably wouldn't pay more than $10 for it, personally."
