76561198070165575,Recommended,224480,10696694,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,MR x DAVIDz,"I believe it was sometime between smashing my own 3-tier wedding cake to the floor and slapping my bride-to-be in the face with a live fish in the first level when I first realized that this is a deliciously entertaining game.The storyline (albeit nonlinear and somewhat confusing at times) is a cute, innocuous little tale that playfully pokes at what could be a much darker, mysterious backstory underneath, without actually delving into it. Instead, the game remains marshmallowy and jubilant with antics such as preparing your own coffee and going grocery shopping... with spaghetti as limbs. The gameplay itself is very entertaining, and believe it or not, the controls (for which I recommend the XBOX 360 controller) contribute a lot to the replayability of this game, even if you can't seem to get used to them.There's no way NOT to get into a giggle fit when you're slithering through the freezers of the frozen food section to get to the last frozen pizza in the supermarket. Few things are funnier than trying to climb UP a DOWN escalator when--let's face it-- you don't even have the ability to walk, nay, *stand* anywhere without falling. One thing is for sure, Octodad: Dadliest Catch reminds you to stop and laugh at yourself every now and then. Which you need sometimes. Because you're a freaking octopus. In a suit. 8/10"
