,Recommended,224480,10819766,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Opal,"Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a unique game, to say the least. Let's cover the good, first.-It's controls are a special kind of awful, but that's the point of the game. The controls are made to be bad, as you control a boneless cephalopod. It makes the gameplay hectic and fun, while still being managable and controllable if you understand the system.-The humor and writing are great. If you like surrealist humor and snappy quotes, this game's writing will appeal to you. Also, the titular character is very likeable, for what he is.-Similarly to Valve's Portal series, the supply of quotes for each stage is full. You'll only run out of clever commentary if you're stuck on a level for longer than you should be.-For a game with about four voice actors, this game's acting is impressive.-The references are very nice, ranging from nods to other games (""MintCraft""), to even YouTubers (""Total Biscuits"")Now, let's go over the less good.-The graphics, while being charming and pleasantly cartoony, are very unimpressive. The human characters' eyes very rarely seem to move, and the textures are very simple.-The game is very, very brief. It can be beaten in one sitting, if you know how to play it. Workshop makes up for that, though.-The soundtrack leaves some room to be desired.If the issues don't overpower the positives of this game for you, then it's worth a play. However, do not buy this at full price. It is too short to warrent it's 15 dollar price tag. If you can catch it on sale, by all means, purchase it. It's still a fun game."
