,Recommended,224480,8939288,"Posted: 1 February, 2014",all,Doskias,"It's hard to explain exactly what this game is. You're a dad in a (mostly) normal American suburb, trying to live your life and help your family. Also you're an octopus, so that makes things a bit more complicated.I guess it's a third-person puzzle game? Maybe? But it's less figuring out what you need to do, and more figuring out how to use the abilities you have to do what you know you need to. It's difficult to explain. It requires the same sort of brain-rewriting and mechanics-unlearning that you went through when you started to get the hang of Surgeon Simulator.It's weird. It's funny. Most importantly, it'sdifferent. I really think anyone and everyone should try it out. It's worth it."
