76561198051958085,Recommended,224480,11480394,"Posted: 30 July, 2014",all,Everyone,"A word ofdadviceto people who like physics and humor: BUY NOW!Whereas most games nowadays content themselves with boring WASD movement controls, Octodad: Dadliest Catch tasks you to walk with the mouse, clicking left or right to lift a foot and then dragging to move the foot. This technically gives you *more* control over Octodad's movement, but his loose and springy body consistently makes this cumbersome in a unique and hilarious way. Simply walking across a room is a joy.Of course, you'll be doing more than just walking. Octodad's double-life requires him to complete many seemingly mundane human tasks that are quite difficult for an octopus. But if you mess things up too much, people around you (including your own family) will begin to start to contemplate the notion that you might possibly, in fact, be an octopus and not a human. These situations are generally very well designed and fun, clumsy as Octodad may be.Physical/gameplay gags aside, the story is chock full of silly, family-friendly humor. Many dialog exchanges are comedy gold. The ridiculous fact that no one knows he's an octopus never got old, in my opinion. The game is not just funny, though. The main story has a strong and sometimes emotional plotline. There were some serious feels towards the end of the game.Some have complained that the main story is too short, clocking in at around two hours at most.This is short for a $15 game, but there is much more content to be had. Free Play allows you to... freely play around in the story levels without the normal restrictions. Steam Workshop support means that you can download all kinds of custom missions, from re-worked versions of existing story missions (zero-gravity? First-Person? check!) to hardcore parkour courses, etc. There's even a full-featured zombie horde survival map available for download, if that's your thing. And with free DLC planned to add more ""canon"" missions to the game, there will be even more polished and goofy fun to be had with Octodad: Dadliest Catch.9/10Would blub again"
