,Recommended,224480,11508114,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,lemmy,"Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a wonderful game in my opinion for a handful of reasons and I will cover all of them in this reviewStoryline length and quality:a common complaint is that the story is short, while i agree with this I also don't really mind the game takes about 2 hours to run through if you don't waste time and run through the game but if you take your time to do what you feel like doing and explore every bit of floppy chaos in a level the game's play time can go up to at least 5 hours. The story itself feels like a movie or a book it's really just wonderful and sort of unique but extremely cliche at the same time without spoiling anything here's the jist of it: you play as octodad an octopus whose family and the rest of humankind (except for a single sushi chef) thinks he's a man just carrying out his daily life.Gameplay/Controls:The gameplay is great and by that i mean the physics are generally pretty good i haven't had anything get stuck in a wall or under a table or whatever. the controls on the other hand are different at first they are kind of hard but after some practice you'll be jiggling around like a pro. it really only took me about 10 minutes to get the controls down but after that it was smooth sailing.Maps:The maps are great they have plenty of props to play with but also AREN'T overflowing with props because that would make it hard to move. most maps have secret areas where you can collect ties which i will get to later.Collectibles:the one thing that annoys me the MOST in games is upgradable skill systems that you need to use to beat the game, octodad on the other hand doesn't have one which makes me VERY happy you can play through without having to spend EXP to get new skills because there are no skill points in-game anyway. the only collectible is ties which are just new ties to wear and look cool.graphics:I have a toaster and can run this at 100 FPS. 'nuff said.Workshop support/Replay value:IMMENSE REPLAY VALUE the game has SO MUCH to do in every level that you really need to replay it at least twice to get all the content in. not to mention this game has workshop support and my overall experience with it: walked into a supermarket naked and stole cereal from a lady.          10/10 for workshop.OVERALL GRADE: 9.5/10reason for not a perfect 10: workshop has skins for octodad but they have to be installed manually but it's not a big deal."
