,Not Recommended,224480,8992378,"Posted: 5 February, 2014",all,Major Triad,"Octodad: Dadliest Catch begins as a quirky and hilarious combination of QWOP and Surgeon Simulator requiring the player to perform simple tasks such as getting dressed and making coffee as a rubber-limbed octopus in disguise. The controls are difficult to use - But that's half the fun.However the game begins to fall flat during and after the Aquarium levels, requiring the player to use stealth to avoid marine biologists and fisherman and turning this silly and fun game in to a tedious, trial-and-error wet paper towel simulator. There's even an entire level dedicated to slowly pushing ""A"" repeatedly to escape a shark. Thrilling.The game is ultimately ruined by the three stealth-centric levels that follow which restrict the player's freedom to flop about and the final boss fight was less-than-enjoyable.To top it all off, the game is only about 2 hours long, most of which is rather forgettable.Octodad: Dadliest Catch was a hilarious game idea that unfortunately wasn't used to its full potential to create a completely enjoyable experience."
