76561198034740265,Recommended,224480,9637664,"Posted: 26 March, 2014",all,Bizarro lexilogo,"This game is really, really good, but it isn't for everyone. The first thing to address here is the movement and controls. It's awkward, but calling it 'deliberately bad' is IMO not really true. It's responsive and precise, but the difficulty comes from the fact that you are an invertebrate rather than that the controls suck. The plot is nothing special, though it did carry more emotional weight than I thought it would. Graphics and voice acting is nothing special, but where the game really shines is it's sense of humour. Most of the reference based jokes are delivered via background objects so as not to confuse people who don't get them, and the chatter from passersby is something I genuinely want to listen to, as it always brings out a smile on my face. However, the gameplay is where this thing really shines. While it doesn't have that much replay value (the game's around 5 hours long assuming you don't rush through all the levels), there are decently hidden secrets to find and loads of little trinkets to grab and mess around with in your environment or just extra stuff to do, though there could potentially be more. Still, this game is just about having stupid fun and messing around, as the gameplay perfectly demonstrates. It composes of you doing ordinary mundane things at the start extremely awkwardly, and ends with you doing out of the ordinary things in ways you couldn't imagine. If you have low amounts of patience or are short on cash and therefore want a timesink, this isn't your game, but this is a nice diversion of a game. It also has Workshop support and a decent supply of nice quality user created levels (as well as some stuff done by the devs demonstrating what can be done in the engine). If you have your doubts you can always download the original Octodad for free and see if the control scheme agrees with you, and honestly, you probably know already if this is a game that you're going to enjoy.In conclusion, this is a game that is designed for people who just like doing stupid things in a game and laughing at it. It doesn't just rely on it's physics engine or controls as some reviews might imply, as it also has an fantastic sense of humour, good music and just an all-round good feel to it. Like I said, you should know if you will enjoy this or hate it. Also, they changed the stealth segments significantly and they now barely involve stealth at all, so you needn't worry about that. And if that isn't enough for you, the devs are planning to port the game to the PS4 with new levels and features and then update the PC version with said bonus goodies! My advice is get your tentacles on this game as soon as possible!"
