76561197990024016,Recommended,224480,8998540,"Posted: 6 February, 2014",all,Aperture Science,"I picked this game up on a whim because I saw it in the featured items section. The odd funny image of an octopus wearing a suit with a family caught my attention. What is this game about? You're just a normal octopus wanting to live the American dream. Having a lovely wife and kids, mowing the lawn, picking up groceries, taking your family to the aquarium, etc. The only problem is that these tasks are incredibly difficult for you to complete (you know, since you're an octopus) so much so that even walking is a challenge. You use your mouse to move the octopus as well as move his hands (press space bar to switch between hands and feet). At first I couldn't help but to laugh at the terrible controls, but that's exactly what makes the game fun. Do note that controlling octodad gets increasingly easier as you play. Reading the reviews from other people on here, the main two negative points I have noticed: *The game is difficult at parts and *There is not enough game for the price.The game is difficult at parts: Yes the game is difficult in the later missions (particularly the very last mission will have you frustrated). However this doesn't take away from the game at all in my opinion. The sneaking parts as some people had problems with were incredibly easy to get past with little to know thinking. Unless you're a 9 year old who has never before played a video game, you won't have a problem with this.There is not enough game for the price: The main game is pretty short yes. I beat the main story in roughly 2-1/2 hours. HOWEVER, each level has 3 hidden ties scattered throughout. You can change your tie once you find a new one. After you beat the game you also unlock freeplay mode which allows you to go back and do any level. Let me just say that this game is FUN and I will definitely come back and play it a few times a week. I bought the game for $11.99 on a steam sale. Would I pay $11.99 for it again? Absoultely I would. The game is plain funny. The kind of funny where you just laugh at how silly it is. An octopus struggling to pour a glass of chocolate milk for his (somehow strangely) 100% human daughter...that's just silly! I enjoyed every bit of this game, even the last (insanely difficult mission)."
