76561198056890154,Recommended,224480,9738181,"Posted: 5 April, 2014",all,Spirit Warden,"I'd give this game a 6.5/10. The game is funny and charming but the leg controls can and will drive you up the walls (if only they did the same for Octodad)! Tasks like climbing up a ladder or walking across thin ledges are almost impossibe because his legs have little traction. Unlike his arms which won't let go of a grabbed item, his legs WILL slide off of surfaces. If his legs simply didn't move once you let go of the button then it would make the game would be less hair-pullingly frustrating and much more enjoyable. Furthermore, you have little control of the camera which makes it hard to see where you are placing Octodads legs in certain camera angles, more control and a zoom fuction would be nice. IF that were the case i'd give it a 10/10 but as of right now I just can't. I would still recommend this game just be prepared to rage at certain times =/"
,Recommended,224480,9738425,"Posted: 5 April, 2014",all,VaultBoy,"Octodad is an a quirky, funny game. The control scheme for the game is unique where you control each leg separately and control one arm. Each leg is tied to a rocker button (LT, RT) and the arm is tied to the 2 analog sticks (to provide 3 dimensional movement). Most of the game has you fumbling around performing tasks like mowing the lawn, buying grocery, or other relatively mundane daily activities. It's the ridiculousness of these things combined with the destruction in Octodad's wake that makes it very fun. Some of the more story-driven elements that require much more precise movement can be a bit unforgiving and it detracts a little from the fun, but overall it's blast to play."
