76561198046371963,Recommended,224480,9172903,"Posted: 18 February, 2014",all,Heavykiin,"In this game you play as a normal, everyday father. Little does your family (and the rest of mankind) know, you are secretly an octopus! Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a sequel to the original Octodad, but sadly i haven't played it. In order to keep his secret, Octodad must complete normal, everyday tasks, such as mowing the lawn, grocery shopping, and surviving a crazed chef determined to expose him and make him into moderately priced sushi rolls. Easy, right? Not really. you must switch between hands mode and legs mode. Legs mode lets you, well, walk! but that's easier said than done. See if you can get the mango soda on the top of the cardboard building at the store on the first try! Hands mode allows you to control Octodad's arms (tentacles really). You can grab something, switch to legs mode and the item will still be in your hand. However, Octodad must always be careful. If he does stuff out of the ordinary, such as knocking his son senseless with a carton of milk, people will become suspicious. if the suspicion levels become too high, Octodad is doomed. This game could possibly make you angry (believe me) you can't help but to come back and help Octodad keep his secret. I can't help but to add Octodad to my list of favorite video game characters. When you feel like it you can play some workshop levels (Windows only i believe). Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a fun, charming game and i don't regret adding it to my library."
