76561198015038674,Recommended,224480,10927525,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,ReanimatedYatzi,"Ragdoll physics. Awkward controls. References to Minecraft, Adventure Time, and the like. All of these things add onto the reason why this game is so pleasant and fun. The story itself isn't terribly great, but most of the dialogue is chuckle-worthy. The music is also charming, with the boss battle music being both epic and funny.However, the game is not without it's faults. The biggest thing is that the game can be beaten in a little over 2 hours at a leisurely pace. This includes some exploring and a few instances of having to restart from checkpoints. It would seem that the replayability of this game lies mostly in finding collectibles and earning the achievements, so if you like that, then the $15 price tag should be worth it. If not, this is would probably only be worth it if one were to pick it up during a Steam Sale.As I mentioned before, the controls are awkward. While they definitely add to the charm of the game, I've only played the game using a controller. I can't imagine the keyboard controls would be any sort of fun (though I'm sure others would disagree), so this might also be something to consider.All in all, I would give this a 4/5, with length being the biggest issue."
