,Recommended,224480,9022406,"Posted: 8 February, 2014",all,The_Manbat™,"A short but hilarious ride.The main idea of Octodad is that you're an octopus trying to blend in as a human while doing every day tasks like grilling burgers or mowing the lawn. Most of the humor comes from Octodad himself as you try to do tasks, nd dancing. The game is really funny. Controlling Octodad is fun (if a little annoying at times) and it's satisfying when you finally make your coffee in the morning. The story is OK, it's not a Mass Effect level of story telling but it gets the job done. Graphics are colorful and nice to look at but a little bit simple. The game is kind of easy except for the final level which is one of the most frustrating levels in video game history. The voice acting is excellent, especilly for Octodad. The game is quite short, it took me 2 hours to finish on normal, however I did not go for the collectibles. The game has good replay value with collectibles, achievements, and steam workshop support.Overall I do recommend this game.   7.5/10+Great Humor+Good Graphics+Good Puzzles and Gameplay+Good Voice Acting+Good Replayibility-Short-Frustrating End level-Octodad is sometimes annoying to control"
