76561198047202396,Recommended,224480,13746597,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,Sola Greylock,"I’ve got to admit, at first I was a little sceptical about this game. The idea of someone being a married father of two kids and an octopus sent alarm bells ringing in my literal mind.However I was soon pulled into the havoc I was able to wreak on the area, despite the high level of awkward which was the controls. I’ll take a guess and say the game was designed to have awkward controls, anyway and try to let it slide but it never really got any easier to control Octodad as time passed, and I wasn’t given nearly enough time to get used to it, anyway, as it took me around three hours to complete the whole thing.But, as I said before, it was a lot of fun to destroy everything in sight and attempt to complete the objectives with the handicap I was given.What I really wanted out of the game was the ability to use the co-op with two mice, struggling with Octodad’s various appendages was hilarious enough on my own, and could only have been funnier wrestling his limbs with another player. But, alas, I do not own the means to play that way.All in all, Octodad was fun while it lasted, but that wasn’t nearly long enough, despite the various maps and levels created by the community.The scores are as follows:Graphics: 6/10-	Graphics were okay but not amazing. Nothing really stood out to me.Music: 8/10-	The music fit the game’s atmosphere well and was enjoyable to listen to. There was nothing that made me want to look it up and listen on repeat, however.Cinematics: 6/10-	Again, nothing really noteworthy here. It was decent but not outstanding.Story: 7/10-	I really enjoyed the story except for the kids. I still can’t get my head wrapped around them but I’m going to take a guess and say that Scarlet wasn’t completely honest with her husband and they could’ve made the transition to the past more obvious. But I found it amusing and enjoyable all the same.Content: 5/10-	There wasn’t nearly enough here to satisfy me. I didn’t have the time to get used to the controls and managed to finish it in a couple of hours.Controls: 5/10-	The reason why this isn’t even lower is that I’m assuming the controls are meant to be awkward and difficult. If not, I have some serious concerns.Gameplay: 7/10-	While I wish I could play co-op with my limited technology, I will say again that causing mayhem and destruction made up for a little of the struggle with controls.Playability: 6/10-	Due to it being quick to complete, I’m sure I’ll find myself staggering though it again at some point however there still wasn’t enough content for me to be fully invested.Value: 5/10-	For a game this short, it seems wrong to charge it for £11.99, not counting community content. The price is a little too high for a game of its length.Personal Opinion: 7/10-	It’s still a well-made game with decent graphics and a fun story. I would play it again.Overall score: 6.2/10Would recommend?Not when it’s full price. Buy it when it’s on sale."
