76561198093385733,Recommended,224480,11138547,"Posted: 8 July, 2014",all,GiftigeCherrie,"I like silly games. And thats exactly what this game is.First thing: this game is not for the impatient. Major tasks are going to take you multiple, frustrating tries and you will get annoyed, but perseverence is key.The game tells of a dear octopus, just trying to live a normal life with his family while avoiding discovery and capture by the evil chef. The story is sweet and endearing. The tasks are everyday things which a human would find easy, but are monumentally difficult for the extra wobbly Octodad. On top of this is the ridiculous fact that despite his less-than-solid form, the NPCs don't know he's not human.The result is a charming game with great personality, challenging enough to keep you going and of course, ripe with hilarity.The only gripe I have is that the playing time of the main story is so short! I would have loved for the story to be longer, perhaps tell of how Octodad came to live as a human.Overall, it's a great game and I would recommend it if you like a good laugh and if you're not bothered about the insanely jelly-like physics of your character."
