,Recommended,224480,8917186,"Posted: 30 January, 2014",all,Professor Smiles,"A Sticky SituationI don't wish to give any spoilers, but suffice it to say Octodad: Dadliest Catch is one of the finest ""slice of life,"" real time, family simulation experiences I have ever found. I played the previous demo iteration multiple times, and found myself often feeling a sense of deja vu. Much of this game and its predecesor mirrors my own life, and I instantly felt a deep blue connection with Octodad as I silently watched him go about his day. His pain was my pain; his trials were my trials.The controls using both Mouse and Keyboard, and with a controller were intuitive and natural. So much so I often forgot where my tentacles, err *blub* fingers ended and the controls began.Not only were the gameplay mechanics incredibly realistic, and a wonderful aspiration for any aspiring shrimp, but the story was a tumultuous sea of plot twists and harrowing escapes. I felt flashbacks to many instances in my own life, and I am sure you will feel the same after playing this game.I cannot recommend this game enough. If I had any criticism to make, it would be that the story could be perhaps 2000 leagues longer, and that I could never see the final reveal coming. At least my family could never see it coming.  *Nervous closing blub*"
