,Recommended,224480,11000785,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Loerwyn,"I'm going to say ""Yes, I recommend Octodad"", but with a few caveats. I think it is something you have to experience (much like its spiritual brothers QWOP, Surgeon Simulator, etc.), yet it goes a little further and I think this does work out as a benefit as much as a flaw.See, my problem with Octodad is that it can be unfair. Yes, it can be challenging and require you to think, but there are moments (particularly towards the end) where the game can sometimes fail to give you a chance or leaves you hanging. I remember on one of the levels I 'died' as soon as a scene changed because it didn't give me a chance to even really think about moving. The 'puzzle' before the final boss is also infuriating.But when Octodad is fun, it is FUN. It can be really, really funny to watch him flail and destroy the environment, but the game is littered with in-jokes, references and spoofs, as well as some collectables and other little things to find.Just... be prepared to throw your controller or tear your hair out."
