76561198108162491,Recommended,224480,11515056,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,forsakenphoenix,"+ Cute, heartwarming story+ Nice soundtrack- Short game- Doesn't seem to like low-end computers from my experienceOverall score: 7/10Now that I've actually been able to finish the game, I've decided to rewrite my review. Playing Octodad is kind of like playing QWOP on steroids. However, Octodad has a much better story, a much better soundtrack, and much better graphics than QWOP could ever hope for. Octodad is interesting since it seems to rely on slapstick humor, something you don't see a lot in video games. However, despite all of its silliness, it manages to tell a very heartwarming story. If these sort of things sound appealing to you, I would give Octodad a go.Unfortunately, the game does come with its downsides. First off, it is a very short game. If I were you, I would wait until a sale because I think that $15 for such a short game is not really worth it. However, the biggest problem I encountered was the fact that I originally bought this game so I could play it on my low-end laptop. To be frank, my laptop certainly wasn't meant for gaming, but it did meet all of the minimum requirements for Octodad. It ran smoothly with no lag, but once I reached the Arcade, the controls weren't responsive enough to beat the games there. I contacted the developer about my issues, but my problems remained a mystery. Thus, if you want to buy this game, I would personally recommend that you play this game on a computer that exceeds the minimum requirements (even if just by a little). Otherwise, you could end up stuck in the Arcade like I was. Also, keep in mind that I tried to struggle through the Arcade for about 3.5 hours. That means that in reality, it didn't really take me 8 hours to beat the game, but more like 4.5-5 hours. However, I didn't go and hunt for all of the hidden ties and achievements. If you want to do that, it would certainly add more play time onto this game.Overall, Octodad was a fun, albeit short adventure. Just be careful if you have a low-end computer."
