,Recommended,224480,10531329,"Posted: 19 June, 2014",all,Bergell ★,"It's probably very marmite, this game. There'll be some people who love the idea of being able to fly around an aquarium as an octopus, rebounding off wall and scenery left and right, and there'll be people who would rather be doing something else.It's a fairly nice game and it actually has a fair balance between this insanity and playing it like a ""normal"" game. The controls aren't exactly precise (well, what the hell did you expect?) to get to grips with, but they're easy to use and adapt to after a while. It also adapts fairly well to how you use it - someone who thrashes around a mouse like a baby does a plastic toy will end up playing the game through completely differently to someone who's more slow with their actions. The graphics are bright and colourful, and while the models aren't the greatest, they aren't really that terrible.The main storyline seems fairly short - you could complete it in a few hours or so if you tried and you could probably manage just shy of two if you don't spend half your time trying to destroy as much as you possibly could. However, the game does allow for the downloading of third-party content through Steam, so once you do complete it there's still more to be had."
