76561198020817552,Recommended,224480,9294001,"Posted: 28 February, 2014",all,Dreadlord Joe,"Octodad: Dadliest Catch is a charming, tongue-in-cheek tale about an octopus pretending to be human. The controls are purposely ridiculous. You flail through getting married, doing chores, shopping and spending quality time with your kids. The graphics are appropriately cartoony, making Octodad more lovable. Some may complain about the stealth sections near the end of the game, but I had no problems with it and even found it enjoyable. The overall length of the story is short, but I couldn't resist going back to get achievements, find ties and try out all of the things being produced in the Steam Workshop. All in all, Octodad: Dadliest Catch has earned its place as one of my favorite games of the year."
