76561198069396993,Not Recommended,224480,19504538,"Posted: 5 December, 2015",all,xShoot4WarAmpsx,"OctoDad: Deadliest Catch Review:So I picked this game up during the Steam Summer sale and just got around to playing it.  I find it to be a decent game but not something worth spending too much money on.So the basis of this game is that you are an octopus pretending to be human and you have a family of humans who have no idea you are an octopus except for on Chef who is out to kill you and eat you. So you spend the entire game basically doing chores. You dress yourself, make coffee, mow the lawn, pick weeds, cut firewood, go grocery shopping and explore and aquarium with your family. There are some puzzles involved with this game. The are mostly trivial to adults.Graphics: 6 - Graphics are nothing special. There is nothing wrong with the Graphics, there is just nothing that wows you. So they are above averageGameplay: 5 - Gameplay itself is pretty cool at first but after a while it kind of wears off. I mean all you do is move your arms and legs and collect things. You can mess around and destroy things but that wears off just as quickly as Goat Simulator does. The other problem I found with this game is that the Keyboard Controls suck. I plugged in my 360 controller 3/4 in and it was so much easier to control. Problem with the keyboard is that it forces you to switch between modes. You cant operate the arms and legs at the same time. The analogs on the controller are also more effencient than moving the mouse. You need a lot of room to move the mouse. The controls are average.Story: 6 - Story is pretty decent. It is obviously not something you should take realistically but it is kind of entertaining but it is extremely short. I mean you could probably beat the game in 1-2 hours. There are really only 5 levels and they are not too long.Replayability: 4 - There are some other modes you can do after you beat the game but I really do not have any interest in playing them. The game has achievements so you will likley play at least 2 playthroughs to collect them all if you are a collector like me but honestly after that I probably will never touch this game again.Summary: Octodad The Deadliest Catch is a average game. It is a short game and I do not feel it is worth the original price. If you can get this game for $5 or less go for it. It is a good game at that price but $10-$15 pass on it. The game is very limited and the novelty of it wears off quickly."
76561197970815119,Recommended,224480,19497918,"Posted: 5 December, 2015",all,cyb-009,"Frustration as entertainment, a weird concept, but in this game it works!Octodad is as difficult to control as you would expect from a creature wit no bone structure, flopping and weaving his way aond the place while knocking things over.But that actually is his charm, since he seams dead set to be the best dad he can be despite his ""handicap"" while preventing others from finding out what he actually is.As you would expect, everything in the game world is cartoonishly weird and the plot fits that feeling well.It's not very long, but it's enjoyable, often frustrating in a fun way and constantly strange.Go for a slither, I think you might enjoy it."
