76561198021084940,Recommended,224480,13717689,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,in-fer-no,"Worth the full price? NoIf not, at what price reduction? 50% or better.Why play this game?It's a silly game with funny physics and also to see the human world through the struggles of an octopus.Problems: None worth mentioning. An gamepad controller is recommended though.Story: You don't really play this game for the story. It was pretty cheesy but it drove the game forward.Mechanics: You control the octopus' body with the keyboard and mouse. Controls are a bit clunky but that's probably intentional. Solve puzzles and have fun with the octopus physics.Playtime/replayability: 2-3 hours. Play by yourself through the story or do missions together with a friend (localy co-op) two people both control different parts of the octopus.Why I recommend it: I would suggest you download  the first octodad game for free and decide if you think the octopus physics is funny. Buy this if you want more of octodad!"
